		"name": "custom_erpnext — Push API (Laravel → ERPNext)",
		"description": "Middleware push endpoints for offline POS / Laravel sync.\n\n## Fix AuthenticationError\nFrappe validates `Authorization: token {api_key}:{api_secret}` against the **User** record `middleware@laravel.local` — not ERPNext login password.\n\n1. Get current credentials (does **not** rotate secret):\n   `bench --site YOUR_SITE execute custom_erpnext.setup.laravel_integration.get_middleware_api_credentials`\n2. Set Postman collection variables `api_key` and `api_secret` exactly from that output.\n3. Header must be exactly: `token KEY:SECRET` (not Bearer).\n4. For first test set `sign_requests` = `false`. Enable `true` once token auth works.\n5. Use the same site URL as bench (`http://tsc.localhost` or your host_name).\n\n**Rotate secret:** `get_middleware_api_credentials` with `rotate_secret=1`.\n\n**ZATCA status** (pull, not push):\n`POST .../custom_erpnext.api.v1.pull.get_sales_invoice_zatca_status`",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
